 , taking the y coordinate as zero, when 
\begin_inset Formula $t=0$
\end_inset

 )
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote
a) For the first 2 sec : 
\begin_inset Formula $\dfrac{\bigtriangleup y}{\bigtriangleup t}=\dfrac{\dfrac{1}{2}\times9.8\times2^{2}-\dfrac{1}{2}\times9.8\times0^{2}}{2-0}=9.8m/s$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote
b) From sec 1 to sec 2 : 
\begin_inset Formula $\dfrac{\bigtriangleup y}{\bigtriangleup t}=\dfrac{\dfrac{1}{2}\times9.8\times2^{2}-\dfrac{1}{2}\times9.8\times1^{2}}{2-1}=14.7m/s$
\end_inset


\end_layout

